node.text:
So this happened…

It’s been exactly a month since my account was hacked. Even though I’m a huge believer of “everything happens for a reason” and trusting God with my path, at times like this it was hard to believe. 

Growing up wasn’t the easiest for me. My mom raising two boys alone where some days it was hard for us to eat, finding out dad wasn’t the person I thought he was, moving to a new country without knowing their language or the culture, I didn’t have any time to find out who I really was. Finding the gym helped me to find myself. Social media helped me to realize I had a purpose in life and one of my dream became reality where I was finally able to take care of my family. Right when I thought all my hard work was paying off it was gone; I felt like a lost kid again. 

As first and second week went by I was losing my faith, hope, and motivation. I was negative, angry, everything that I never wanted to be. Not only that but I was affecting the people around me that I care and love. Thank God something clicked inside of my head before things could’ve gone worse. I realized this was just another battle/“test” life was giving me and important lesson that God is trying to teach me.

During my third and fourth week I learn to leave all this to God, he had a plan for me while I was learning about myself and life. I learn how to let go of those negative feels when unexpected negative things happen in my life, to always stay grateful and thankful to things I get use to having, to forgive people on their poor actions or mistakes they make such as the hacker. I can go on and on about lessons I learned but my main point was to share a message and thank every single one of you guys. 

You guys made my impossibles to possibles. Your support changed my life. I was able to accomplish dreams I always dreamed of. Word “thank you” doesn’t describe how thankful I am for every single one of you guys. When bad happens in ur life, it’s hard to believe that this was meant to happen, don’t u worry. God has a plan for u and he will always do what’s best for u.

Thank u @gymshark @jbenchampion for helping to get my account back. We back! Time to grind💪🏼
(Swipe for a surprise)
